<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 15 at 5:51PM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Portage
and east central Summit Counties through 630 PM EDT...
At 551 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Kent, or 8 miles west of Ravenna, moving southeast at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Winds up to 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Akron, Ravenna, Cuyahoga Falls, Kent, Tallmadge, Streetsboro,
Mogadore, Stow, Brimfield, Munroe Falls, Lakemore, Silver Lake, Brady
Lake and Sugar Bush Knolls.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
